ent of the Dog in the Night-Time\n|\nTruth must be found in reality, not systems.\n\n- Joseph Beuys, What Is Art?: Conversations with Joseph Beuys\n|\nLife is supposed to be exciting, so journey through each day collecting moments and celebrating the right ones.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nEvery challenge you face today makes you stronger tomorrow. The challenge of life is intended to make you better, not bitter.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nAn idea, like a ghost, must be spoken to a little before it will explain itself.\n\n- Charles\n|\nYou wanna fly, you got to give up the shit that weighs you down.\n\n- Toni Morrison, Song of Solomon\n|\nYou were born to stand out, stop trying to fit in.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nJust when you think you're in the cat-bird's seat, the Angel of Death calls 'dibs' on shotgun.\n\n- P.L.\n|\nWhen you've understood this scripture, throw it away. If you can't understand this scripture, throw it away. I insist on your freedom.\n\n- Jack Kerouac, The Scripture of the Golden Eternity\n|\nEvery word Martone sets down, finally, a choice that limits the universe, their trail across the page a fossil record of some life's life-story.\n\n- Michael Martone, Michael Martone\n|\nTotal knowledge is annihilation Of the desire to see, to touch, to feel The world sensed only through senses And immune to the knowledge without feeling.\n\n- Dejan\n|\nO rose, you look sick.O rose, wake up and sing.\n\n- Santosh Kalwar, I Am Dead Man Alive\n|\nIf your wife locks you out of the house, you don't have a problem with your door.\n\n- Anne Lamott, Bird by Bird: Some Instructions on Writing and Life\n|\nIn the bleak midwinter Frosty wind made moan, Earth stood hard as iron, Water like a stone; Snow had fallen, Snow on snow, Snow on snow, In the bleak midwinter, Long ago.\n\n- Christina Rossetti, The Poetical Works of Christina Georgina Rossetti\n|\nThe thing about getting older is that you don't need everything to be possible any more, you just need things to be certain.\n\n- Monica Ali, Brick Lane\n|\nEach friend represents a world in us, a world possibly not born until they arrive, and it is only by this meeting that a new world is born.\n\n- Anaïs Nin, The Diary of Anaïs Nin, Vol. 1: 1931-1934\n|\nWe fall from womb to tomb, from one blackness and toward another, remembering little of the one and knowing nothing of the other ... except through faith.\n\n- Stephen King, Danse Macabre\n|\nIn my quest to search for knowledge, I know God, the source of knowledge.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nWe all can be only who we are, no more, no less.\n\n- Terry Goodkind, Stone of Tears\n|\nSufism,' according to the Sufi, 'is an adventure in living, necessary adventure.\n\n- Idries Shah, The Sufis\n|\n...required for good fiction: character, conflict, change through time. And if you're really blessed, you get resolution. But life doesn't usually work out that way.\n\n- Ted\n|\nI am tired, Beloved, of chafing my heart againstThe want of you;Of squeezing it into little inkdrops,And posting it.\n\n- Amy\n|\nThe more you can have control over your ego rather than let it run amuck, the more successful you’ll be in all areas of life.\n\n- Roy\n|\nHappiness earned, not given.\n\n- Toba Beta, My Ancestor Was an Ancient Astronaut\n|\nMusic, my rampart and my only one.\n\n- Edna\n|\nEveryone on earth is afraid of losing his/her life, and only a few are afraid of losing their time.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nYou hardly know me. Why do you want me to come with you?''Who knows? Perhaps you remind me just a bit of—''Someone you used to know?' Alec interjected skepti\n\n- Lynn Flewelling, Luck in the Shadows\n|\nWhat difference makes what you believe? What happens will happen anyway, exactly the same, no matter what you believe. What you do makes the important part. What you do.\n\n- Roland Merul