n when it could be turned into momentum.\n\n- Frances\n|\nSeed becomes tree, son becomes stranger.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nSuccess is like water, the more thirsty you are for it is the more you will drink it, and you'll need it forever to survive.\n\n- Werley Nortreus, Best Quotes of Werley Nortreus\n|\nTime, the spaces of light and dark, had long since lost orderliness.\n\n- William Faulkner, Light in August\n|\nFollow your heart, listen to your inner voice, stop caring what others think.\n\n- Roy\n|\nIf you spend your life sparing people’s feelings and feeding their vanity, you get so you can’t distinguish what should be respected in them.\n\n- F. Scott Fitzgerald, Tender is the Night & The Last Tycoon\n|\nI guess a bit part of serious fiction’s purpose is to give the reader, who like all of us is sort of marooned in her own skull, to give her imaginative access to other selves.\n\n- David"